{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"08fb4453-1bad-4a45-a344-c240e23c9832","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 (4.x) dropped support for .NET 6.0 — it requires **net8.0** or later.\n\nYour options:\n\n1. **Upgrade your target framework** to `net8.0` (or `net9.0`), then upgrade MSTest to 4.x.\n2. **Stay on net6.0** and remain on MSTest 3.x. Note that .NET 6 itself is already out of support (EOL November 2024).\n\nThe recommended path is to retarget to `net8.0`+ and then upgrade MSTest. Your test code (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert`) is simple and won't need changes — the MSTest v4 API is backwards-compatible at that level.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"175d8b12-cd42-498c-9b8f-74678b0feb92","outputTokens":189},"id":"e97e64b5-4812-4309-a5cf-99de0beda416","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:07.238Z","parentId":"6393e070-8321-4d46-ba6f-de76ab9843df"}
